Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.82,0:00:18.41,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sein!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.18,0:00:27.50,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,That mage said they'd take our photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.50,0:00:31.46,Flashback,YOUNG SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,A photo? What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.27,0:00:48.43,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.17,0:00:57.35,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,This is the start of our legend!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.52,0:01:28.02,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Like a fairy tale
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.02,0:01:30.44,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sign the story has reached its end
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.44,0:01:33.36,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Like a single passage taken from
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.36,0:01:34.99,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,A journey that was too long
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.99,0:01:37.32,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Of the evil that once cast a shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.32,0:01:39.66,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Across this land
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.66,0:01:41.99,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And the memories of the short journey
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.99,0:01:44.45,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With the hero who defeated it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.25,0:01:54.21,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,473)\blur0.25\fs25\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\pos(322,230)\c&HFFFCFE&\t(989,4326,\c&HEFC777&)\t(6411,6745,\c&HEAC732&)}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.46,0:01:56.76,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The story ends
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.76,0:01:59.26,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And the hero goes to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.26,0:02:02.10,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving this land with
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.10,0:02:03.76,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Days of peace and quiet
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.76,0:02:06.27,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The passage of time heartlessly
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.27,0:02:08.44,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Makes people forget
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.44,0:02:11.23,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the tracks left behind by his life
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.23,0:02:13.02,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Begin to rust
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.02,0:02:14.86,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Just the same
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.86,0:02:17.15,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your words and wishes and courage
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.15,0:02:20.49,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Are still inside of me
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.49,0:02:22.37,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And they live on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.16,0:02:24.91,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We chose the same path
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.91,0:02:27.04,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,That's all it was supposed to be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.04,0:02:28.58,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it that at some point
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.58,0:02:32.84,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to understand the reason for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.84,0:02:34.21,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The tears that fall down my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.21,0:02:35.30,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even now
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.30,0:02:37.67,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,If I retrace the journey we walked together
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.67,0:02:41.22,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you're not there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.22,0:02:42.89,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'll be able to find it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.02,0:02:58.03,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(397,269.5)}Episode 16: Long-Lived Friends
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.03,0:03:03.03,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,16)}29 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Nin the Klar region, located in the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:06.06,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Is he really a strong warrior?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.68,0:03:10.42,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He's a dwarf who's protected the village \Nwe're heading to for almost 400 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.73,0:03:14.35,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What's the life expectancy of dwarves?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.35,0:03:16.42,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,About 300 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.88,0:03:18.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,His name is Old Man Voll.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.75,0:03:20.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He's a long-lived friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.21,0:03:24.24,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I want to chat with him before he dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.24,0:03:26.15,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's not funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.78,0:03:33.55,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But it's true that there aren't many people \Nwho can talk about the past with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.92,0:03:37.26,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps a detour like this one \Nisn't so bad once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.93,0:03:40.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll stay for a decade or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.79,0:03:42.74,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We're staying one week at most.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.55,0:04:05.23,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,That's the village?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.07,0:04:12.21,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Old Man Voll.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.82,0:04:15.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.76,0:04:21.34,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Doesn't he seem cool, \Nlike an old, seasoned warrior?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.34,0:04:23.32,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,He's way beyond old.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.72,0:04:28.89,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Remind me. Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.89,0:04:30.38,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,He's totally decrepit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.83,0:04:32.37,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.76,0:04:36.82,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.99,0:04:41.39,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're still pretending to be senile?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.01,0:04:44.77,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.80,0:04:52.97,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Most deaths in battle \Nare due to carelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:57.10,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,It's the greatest weakness \Nof both demons and people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.46,0:05:00.11,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Can't stand, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.48,0:05:04.99,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Even the most experienced warriors \Ncan easily suffer fatal injuries
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.99,0:05:08.32,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,if they're not attempting \Nto defend themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.81,0:05:14.03,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd drawn my sword then, \Nyou'd be short one leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.74,0:05:17.64,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Your strategies are as underhanded as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.72,0:05:20.01,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.35,0:05:24.36,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,You are welcome here. Make yourself at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.34,0:05:27.99,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.13,0:05:30.33,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I can't walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:34.64,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Stark, train with him while you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.12,0:05:35.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.51,0:05:38.95,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,He's one heck of an old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.02,0:05:42.56,Default,FRONT DESK,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome to use this firewood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.13,0:05:47.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to stay here for a decade. \NFind us some work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.26,0:05:50.45,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, we're only \Nstaying up to one week.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.37,0:05:52.81,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.52,0:06:11.17,Default,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,It's a small village.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.74,0:06:15.52,Default,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,No one else would take the job, \Nso I appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.52,0:06:17.49,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like we have anything else to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.66,0:06:22.92,Default,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I had no idea \NOld Man Voll had friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.92,0:06:26.20,Default,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen him converse \Nso happily before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.84,0:06:28.75,Default,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,He's a senile old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.75,0:06:30.71,Default,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,Normally he struggles \Nto hold a conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.77,0:06:37.66,Default,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,He's protected the village from monsters and \Ndemons for years, but nobody knows why.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.32,0:06:41.18,Default,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,He's like our protective deity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.32,0:06:44.57,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,He's been alone this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.06,0:07:26.51,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A week flies by, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.85,0:07:28.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,How is Stark?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:31.75,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Humans develop quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.33,0:07:34.35,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,He's improved a fair bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:35.55,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.37,0:07:40.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I had fun, Old Man Voll.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.71,0:07:44.46,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really grateful to you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.02,0:07:49.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're the reason I got to know \NHimmel and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.96,0:07:53.92,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Old Man Voll, why do you \Ndefend this village?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.71,0:07:56.91,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,It's ancient history now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.43,0:08:00.13,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.61,0:08:03.62,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,People don't risk their lives \Nfor things that don't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.09,0:08:13.91,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just defending the village my wife loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.14,0:08:19.19,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,She was a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.13,0:08:26.72,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm merely keeping the promise \NI made a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.17,0:08:32.23,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,But I won't say more on the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.43,0:08:39.44,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't adequately describe \Nher face, or voice, or eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.84,0:08:42.87,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,This is my memory alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.86,0:08:47.18,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,It's silly, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.18,0:08:51.91,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I've been keeping a promise \NI made to a dead woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.09,0:08:54.59,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.51,0:09:03.84,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure she's glad \Nyou're keeping your promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.09,0:09:10.45,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel, you're a good hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.45,0:09:13.50,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll defeat the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.27,0:09:21.75,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,My wife wished to see the era of peace that \Ncomes after the defeat of the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.68,0:09:29.01,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I'll carry the memory of the great \Nhero Himmel into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.52,0:09:34.20,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate it, but you \Ndon't have to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.05,0:09:38.42,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I have Frieren and Eisen in my party.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.89,0:09:41.52,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I won't live as long as an elf.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.96,0:09:44.52,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Then it'll be Frieren's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.61,0:09:49.30,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,She'll carry our memory into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.08,0:09:51.03,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.50,0:09:53.27,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:55.88,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.50,0:09:59.92,Flashback,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,You've been blessed with good companions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.49,0:10:03.41,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Later, I'll have to show you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.64,0:10:07.71,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,the collection of handsome poses \NI came up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.71,0:10:10.18,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, maybe I won't remember you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.12,0:10:17.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I probably didn't need that collection \Nof handsome poses after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.66,0:10:19.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I wasted my memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.53,0:10:23.81,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember that hero's face?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.97,0:10:26.34,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.72,0:10:27.91,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,And his voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.09,0:10:32.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't insult me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.23,0:10:34.02,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I remember everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.50,0:10:37.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel is the reason I decided \NI'd get to know people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.60,0:10:42.12,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Like your reason for defending this village,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.42,0:10:43.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,it's important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.23,0:10:48.43,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I see. A reason, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.31,0:10:53.47,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I can't remember anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.10,0:10:58.97,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Not her face, nor her voice, nor her eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.76,0:11:07.34,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,But I continue defending this village \Nfor an important something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.49,0:11:13.30,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite the jokester, Old Man Voll.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.48,0:11:20.83,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, where are you headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.83,0:11:24.84,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're heading to Aureole, \Nthe land where souls rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.41,0:11:27.03,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Where is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.38,0:11:30.49,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Ende, where the Demon King's castle is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.01,0:11:32.28,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.64,0:11:38.07,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,So you're finally off \Nto defeat the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.77,0:11:44.76,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I hope that brings peace to the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.48,0:11:53.19,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Old Man Voll, the Demon King is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.77,0:12:05.09,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.41,0:12:11.44,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll carry your memory into the future, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.37,0:12:18.26,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't mind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.20,0:12:26.65,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad I got to see you \Nat the end of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.65,0:12:30.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You said the same thing eighty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.00,0:12:42.36,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Old Man Voll. Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.02,0:12:45.24,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.48,0:12:49.53,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,I dreamed of my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.35,0:12:51.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.55,0:12:57.38,Default,VOLL,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's because you and I \Nreminisced about the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.34,0:13:00.47,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.01,0:13:14.52,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,124.5)}29 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Non Rohr Road, located in the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.01,0:13:24.30,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Were you asking him something?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.76,0:13:26.54,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.51,0:13:31.79,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,You remember why I'm on \Nthis journey, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.35,0:13:35.66,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it to travel with a sexy older woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.15,0:13:38.67,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,That's important, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.11,0:13:42.67,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,But this is the goal of my journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.49,0:13:47.30,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,To reunite with my friend \Nwho departed ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.30,0:13:49.32,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.62,0:13:53.57,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,A photo? You don't see those often.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.36,0:13:58.14,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,It was taken by a mage who visited \Nmy village a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.23,0:14:01.52,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Have you figured out where he went?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.52,0:14:06.00,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,We've been traveling along major \Nroads in the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.51,0:14:08.94,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Along the way, we've met \Npeople who have seen him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.39,0:14:12.17,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,We can probably keep heading north.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.64,0:14:17.20,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That was ten years ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.20,0:14:19.89,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised anyone remembers seeing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.89,0:14:21.95,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,He has a unique name.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.35,0:14:23.99,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,It leaves a strong impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.69,0:14:26.21,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.70,0:14:28.44,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Gorilla Warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.24,0:14:33.21,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.81,0:14:35.85,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,So what's his real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.30,0:14:39.34,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,His real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.34,0:14:41.31,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you guys were best friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.60,0:14:45.93,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone in the village always \Ncalled him Gorilla Warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.93,0:14:48.73,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, he made them call him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.73,0:14:50.61,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,How does that even happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.36,0:14:54.83,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, I'm Goatee Priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.83,0:14:56.11,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,No one asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.48,0:14:59.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Did people call you that even \Nbefore you could grow a goatee?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.77,0:15:01.82,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Are we still talking about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.37,0:15:06.77,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, it's good enough if they \Nrecognize the name Gorilla Warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.77,0:15:09.39,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,He'd definitely be calling himself that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.03,0:15:11.39,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like a weird guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.65,0:15:14.77,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He's a weird guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.84,0:15:26.09,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Once we cross this canyon \Nand walk for about a week,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.09,0:15:28.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,we'll finally be in the \Nmagical city of Äußerst.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:33.15,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This really has been a long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.15,0:15:34.88,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking at me for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.40,0:15:38.51,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do anything wrong this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.17,0:15:41.70,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Can we stop by a village first?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.01,0:15:45.04,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,The road branches here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:48.21,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. We'd like to rest, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.89,0:15:57.22,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Ten years ago, did someone who called \Nhimself "Gorilla" come this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.62,0:15:59.49,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's a wild question.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.49,0:16:02.15,Default,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you must mean Mr. Gorilla Warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.15,0:16:03.69,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, he knows who that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.69,0:16:07.06,Default,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,I remember him, since he \Nleft a strong impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.06,0:16:10.30,Default,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,He defeated a monster that \Nappeared near the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.70,0:16:13.63,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know which way he headed after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.63,0:16:15.58,Default,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.57,0:16:17.29,Default,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.60,0:16:22.35,Default,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Gorilla seemed close with the stubborn \Nold woman who lives on the plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.35,0:16:24.02,Default,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,You should ask her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.02,0:16:27.65,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,"Stubborn old woman"? \NThat's quite the nickname.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.67,0:16:31.69,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a stubborn old woman, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.90,0:16:34.36,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not telling you for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.36,0:16:36.85,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,She even calls herself stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.85,0:16:38.43,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.83,0:16:46.45,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,You'll perform several tasks for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.93,0:16:52.87,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,First, deliver this letter to Nagel, \Na blacksmith in the neighboring town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.44,0:16:57.33,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a simple errand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.63,0:17:00.08,Default,FREIREN,0000,0000,0000,,It reminds me of my journey with Himmel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.56,0:17:02.83,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You did things like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.63,0:17:07.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Helping people by running errands \Nwas a daily occurrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.85,0:17:13.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,And it always turned into troublesome \Nsearches or monster hunts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.42,0:17:16.52,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Don't jinx us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.24,0:17:21.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, let's do what we can \Nto get her to open up to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.65,0:17:51.04,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,This old woman just refuses to open up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.04,0:17:53.88,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,They don't call her stubborn for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.19,0:18:00.00,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Himmel or Heiter could've \Ngotten her to open up in half a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.00,0:18:03.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But our party only has \Nsocially awkward members.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.52,0:18:09.00,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,This is the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.00,0:18:12.52,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,Polish the heroes' statue in the canyon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.11,0:18:16.88,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me. I'll show you the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.91,0:18:19.86,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What heroes' statue?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.86,0:18:25.42,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a stone statue of the heroes said \Nto have saved the world a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.69,0:18:28.03,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.04,0:18:33.01,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,They're forgotten heroes. \NNo one even knows their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.01,0:18:35.60,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,The village has been looking \Nafter it for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.00,0:18:38.59,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Forgotten heroes, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.59,0:18:41.80,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, you're Goatee Priest, \Naren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.44,0:18:44.94,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,How'd you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:50.70,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,We're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.59,0:18:54.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A priest and a warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.32,0:18:57.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty old.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.67,0:19:01.27,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,They kind of look like Mr. Sein \Nand Mr. Gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.27,0:19:05.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I think I recognize the warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.70,0:19:08.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's Kraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.96,0:19:10.80,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.80,0:19:11.96,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It looks just like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.06,0:19:17.55,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we get started?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.02,0:19:24.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Sein?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.15,0:19:25.48,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.98,0:19:28.79,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,So this person's name is Kraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.33,0:19:30.42,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,What about this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.42,0:19:32.47,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.49,0:19:34.80,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.78,0:19:40.60,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,What's this statue?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.60,0:19:42.59,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't they look just like us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.71,0:19:47.53,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,According to the chief, \Nthey're ancient heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.53,0:19:50.00,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,But nobody even remembers their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.49,0:19:52.82,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,We won't end up like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.82,0:19:54.99,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to be forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.29,0:20:00.31,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to become \Nan unforgettable hero like Himmel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.86,0:20:06.81,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Even the greatest heroes \Nare forgotten someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.29,0:20:12.01,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Even Himmel, who defeated the \NDemon King, will be no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.75,0:20:17.84,Flashback,YOUNG SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right. It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.49,0:20:24.25,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,You think I could get this big \Nif I worked out hard enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.31,0:20:28.04,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,Gorilla Warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.41,0:20:30.63,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, that's my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.27,0:20:34.79,Flashback,YOUNG SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.09,0:20:39.91,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,If I want to become an unforgettable hero, \Nthen I need a memorable name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.36,0:20:45.57,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.51,0:20:49.71,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Then your name is Goatee Priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.89,0:20:55.60,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,That's a great name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.73,0:20:59.60,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure a goatee would look good on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.24,0:21:07.04,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.33,0:21:09.13,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,That was a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.13,0:21:12.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We could've used magic if it \Nwere a bronze statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.61,0:21:16.04,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,I asked Gorilla to polish it, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.04,0:21:19.45,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,but he didn't do as good a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.04,0:21:22.67,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,His only strength is fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:26.94,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,But his name sure was memorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.06,0:21:32.93,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,Gorilla talked about you a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.24,0:21:40.13,Default,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,He said the two of you would become heroes \Nwhose names would be remembered forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.44,0:22:02.55,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you figure out where Gorilla went?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.38,0:22:05.47,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Tür.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.12,0:22:09.42,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a trading city in the middle \Nof the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.42,0:22:11.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's a long ways east from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.18,0:22:15.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's in the opposite \Ndirection from Äußerst.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.96,0:22:17.06,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.71,0:22:23.89,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,What am I going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.03,0:22:28.57,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And you alright
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.07,0:22:31.08,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Can you hear me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.87,0:22:37.96,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Trailing along deserted train tracks
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.96,0:22:40.29,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Crying excessively
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.88,0:22:43.46,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Wanting you to smile
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.46,0:22:49.51,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I hold on to memories I'd like to keep fresh
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.51,0:22:53.22,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.22,0:22:55.98,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With words more precious than a goodbye
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.98,0:23:01.65,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Unremarkable yet special
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.65,0:23:05.19,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.19,0:23:08.24,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.24,0:23:12.99,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.99,0:23:19.08,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if I were to be born again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.08,0:23:24.92,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I would surely choose this place once more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.92,0:23:30.93,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.93,0:23:36.68,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never let you go, I'd choose the present
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.68,0:23:39.64,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if no promises were made
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.64,0:23:42.34,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I'm lost in days of loneliness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.34,0:23:48.69,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears will be alright, \Ndawn will surely break
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.69,0:23:51.37,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm whispering our lullaby
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.37,0:23:55.38,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,for you to come back home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.20,0:23:58.87,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Join me in the other room, one at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.63,0:23:59.45,DefaultOverlap,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Make yourselves at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.14,0:23:58.87,DefaultTop,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.87,0:24:01.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Because mediating is a priest's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.47,0:24:01.80,DefaultOverlap,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,The medicine is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.67,0:24:01.80,DefaultTop,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're embarrassing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.80,0:24:04.24,Default,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty handsome when \NI'm being considerate, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.26,0:24:04.57,DefaultTop,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's not so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.04,0:24:05.99,Signs_NextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,1)\blur3\t(20,312,\blur0.2)\pos(320,113.5)\c&H000000&\t(312,646,\c&HF6F6F6&)\fsp1.6\t(\fsp1)}Episode 17\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NTake Care
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.57,0:24:05.91,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Take care, then.